"Path and file name of a ngIRCd key file containing individual channel keys "
"for different users.  Refer to @samp{man 5 ngircd.conf} for more details."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsubheading
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31390
#, no-wrap
msgid "Pounce Service"
msgstr ""

#. type: cindex
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31393
#, no-wrap
msgid "bouncer, IRC"
msgstr ""

#. type: cindex
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31394
#, no-wrap
msgid "Bounced Network Connection, BNC"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31398
msgid ""
"@url{https://git.causal.agency/pounce/about/, pounce} is a multi-client, "
"TLS-only IRC bouncer.  It maintains a persistent connection to an IRC "
"server, acting as a proxy and buffer for a number of clients."
msgstr ""

#. type: defvar
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31399
#, no-wrap
msgid "pounce-service-type"
msgstr ""

#. type: defvar
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31403
msgid ""
"This is the service type for the pounce IRC bouncer.  Its value is a "
"@code{pounce-configuration} configuration instance, which is documented "
"below."
msgstr ""

#. type: cindex
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31404
#, no-wrap
msgid "IRC bouncer configuration for Libera.Chat"
msgstr ""

#. type: cindex
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31405
#, no-wrap
msgid "Libera.Chat, IRC bouncer configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: defvar
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31420
msgid ""
"The following example configures pounce to act as an IRC bouncer for the "
"@url{https://libera.chat, Libera.Chat} server, using @acronym{CertFP, client"
" certificate fingerprint} authentication to avoid leaking a sensitive "
"password to the publicly readable store.  The equally sensitive TLS "
"certificate file should be created in-place or transferred using a secure "
"means such as SSH, prior to deploying the service.  The service activation "
"will ensure the ownership and permissions of the certificate/key files are "
"set correctly.  In the below example, it is placed at "
"@file{/etc/pounce/libera.pem} on the target machine.  Pounce itself can be "
"used to generate a TLS certificate, using the @samp{pounce -g libera.pem} "
"command, which concatenates both the private key and the public certificate "
"in the specified file name.  For more information regarding CertFP "
"authentication, refer to @samp{man pounce} or the Libera.Chat guide at "
"@url{https://libera.chat/guides/certfp}."
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31428
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(service pounce-service-type\n"
"         (pounce-configuration\n"
"          (host \"irc.libera.chat\")\n"
"          (client-cert \"/etc/pounce/libera.pem\")\n"
"          (nick \"hannah\")\n"
"          (join (list \"#gnu\" \"#guix\" \"#guile\" \"#hurd\"))))\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: defvar
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31444
msgid ""
"Once deployed on the target machine, pounce will act as an IRC server "
"listening for TLS connections on the 6697 TCP port of the @samp{localhost} "
"address of that machine.  By default, a self-signed certificate for pounce "
"is created at @file{/var/lib/pounce/.config/pounce/localhost.cert}.  If you "
"plan to expose the bouncer to the public Internet, it is advisable to use a "
"@acronym{CA, Certificate Authority}-signed certificate, as can be obtained "
"using a certificate service (@pxref{Certificate Services}), so that IRC "
"clients can verify the certificate out of the box.  If you instead plan to "
"connect to the bouncer strictly via a secure connection, for example using a"
" @acronym{VPN, Virtual Private Network} or @acronym{SSH, Secure Shell}, then"
" it is acceptable to simply let your IRC client trust the auto-generated, "
"self-signed pounce certificate or even disable TLS certificate verification "
"in your client."
msgstr ""

#. type: cindex
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31445
#, no-wrap
msgid "IRC bouncer configuration for OFTC"
msgstr ""

#. type: cindex
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31446
#, no-wrap
msgid "OFTC, IRC bouncer configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: defvar
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31456
msgid ""
"To connect to a second server, a second pounce instance is needed, taking "
"care to specify the @code{provision} field of its @code{pounce-"
"configuration} to avoid a name clash with the previous service, along with a"
" distinct @code{local-port} and @code{log-file}.  The following example "
"shows how to configure another bouncer, this time for the "
"@url{https://www.oftc.net, OFTC} IRC server.  Like in the previous example, "
"CertFP authentication is used, which can be configured similarly.  For more "
"details about using CertFP with the OFTC IRC server, refer to "
"@url{https://www.oftc.net/NickServ/CertFP/}."
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31467
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(service pounce-service-type\n"
"         (pounce-configuration\n"
"          (shepherd-provision '(pounce-oftc))\n"
"          (local-port 6698)\n"
"          (log-file \"/var/log/pounce-oftc.log\")\n"
"          (host \"irc.oftc.net\")\n"
"          (client-cert \"/etc/pounce/oftc.pem\")\n"
"          (nick \"sena\")\n"
"          (join (list \"#gcc\" \"#glibc\"))))\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: deftp
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31474
#, no-wrap
msgid "{Data Type} pounce-configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: deftp
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31476
msgid "Available @code{pounce-configuration} fields are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31478
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{pounce} (default: @code{pounce}) (type: file-like)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31480
msgid "The @code{pounce} package to use."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31481
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"@code{shepherd-provision} (default: @code{(pounce)}) (type: list-of-symbols)"
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31487
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{log-file} (default: @code{\"/var/log/pounce.log\"}) (type: string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31489
msgid "The log file name to use."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31490
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{verbose?} (type: maybe-boolean)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31492
msgid "When true, log IRC messages to standard output."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31493
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{local-host} (default: @code{\"localhost\"}) (type: maybe-string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31495
msgid "The host to bind to."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31496
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{local-port} (default: @code{6697}) (type: maybe-port)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31498
msgid "The port to bind to."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31499
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{local-ca} (type: maybe-string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31504
msgid ""
"Require clients to authenticate using a TLS client certificate either "
"contained in or signed by a certificate in the file loaded from @code{local-"
"ca}, a file name.  The file is reloaded when the SIGUSR1 signal is received."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31505
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{local-cert} (type: maybe-string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31511
msgid ""
"File name of the TLS certificate to load.  The file is reloaded when the "
"SIGUSR1 signal is received.  Unless specified, a self-signed certificate is "
"generated at @file{/var/lib/pounce/.config/pounce/@var{host}.pem}, where "
"@var{host} corresponds to the value of the @code{local-host} field."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31512
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{local-priv} (type: maybe-string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31516
msgid ""
"File name of the private TLS key to load.  Unless specified, a key is "
"generated at @file{/var/lib/pounce/.config/pounce/@var{host}.key}, where "
"@var{host} corresponds to the value of the @code{local-host} field."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31517
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{local-pass} (type: maybe-string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31520
msgid ""
"Require the server password pass for clients to connect.  The pass string "
"must be hashed using @samp{pounce -x}."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31521
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{size} (default: @code{4096}) (type: maybe-power-of-two)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31525
msgid ""
"Set the number of messages contained in the buffer to @var{size}.  This sets"
" the maximum number of recent messages which can be relayed to a "
"reconnecting client.  The size must be a power of two."
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31530
msgid ""
"Host to bind the @emph{source} address to when connecting to the server.  To"
" connect from any address over IPv4 only, use @samp{0.0.0.0}.  To connect "
"from any address over IPv6 only, use @samp{::}."
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31533
msgid "The host name to connect to."
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31536
msgid "The port number to connect to."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31537
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{pass} (type: maybe-string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31540
msgid ""
"Password to use to log in with the server.  The password must have been "
"hashed via the @samp{pounce -x} command."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31541
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{join} (type: maybe-list-of-strings)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31543
msgid "The list of channels to join."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31544 guix-git/doc/guix.texi:46123
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{mode} (type: maybe-string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31546
msgid "The user mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31547 guix-git/doc/guix.texi:45177
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:51410 guix-git/doc/guix.texi:51441
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:52322
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{user} (type: maybe-string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31549
msgid ""
"To set the username.  The default username is the same as the nickname."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31550
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{nick} (default: @code{\"pounce\"}) (type: maybe-string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31552
msgid "Set nickname to @var{nick}."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31553
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{real} (type: maybe-string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31555
msgid "Set the real name.  The default is @code{nick}."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31556
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{away} (type: maybe-string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31559
msgid ""
"The away status to use when no clients are connected and no other away "
"status has been set."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31560
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{quit} (type: maybe-string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31562
msgid "The message to use when quitting."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31563
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{no-names?} (type: maybe-boolean)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31567
msgid ""
"Do not request @samp{NAMES} for each channel when a client connects.  This "
"avoids already connected clients receiving unsolicited responses but "
"prevents new clients from populating user lists."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31568
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{queue-interval} (default: @code{200}) (type: maybe-number)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31572
msgid ""
"Set the server send queue interval in milliseconds.  The queue is used to "
"send automated messages from pounce to the server.  Messages from clients "
"are sent to the server directly."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31573
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{trust} (type: maybe-string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31576
msgid ""
"File name of a certificate to trust.  When used, server name verification is"
" disabled."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31577
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{client-cert} (type: maybe-string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31583
msgid ""
"The file name of the TLS client.  If the private key is in a separate file, "
"it is loaded with @code{client-priv}.  With @code{sasl-external?}, "
"authenticate using SASL EXTERNAL.  Certificates can be generated with "
"@samp{pounce -g}.  For more details, refer to ``Generating Client "
"Certificates'' in @samp{man 1 pounce}."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31584
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{client-priv} (type: maybe-string)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31586
msgid "The file name of the TLS client private key."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31587
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{sasl-plain} (type: maybe-pair)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31591
msgid ""
"A pair of the username and password in plain text to authenticate using SASL"
" PLAIN.  Since this method requires the account password in plain text, it "
"is recommended to use CertFP instead with @code{sasl-external}."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31592
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{sasl-external?} (type: maybe-boolean)"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31595
msgid ""
"Authenticate using SASL EXTERNAL, also known as CertFP.  The TLS client "
"certificate is loaded from @code{client-cert}."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsubheading
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:31603
#, no-wrap
msgid "Quassel Service"
