#. type: subsubheading
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43347
#, no-wrap
msgid "Shared Cache Service"
msgstr ""

#. type: cindex
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43348
#, no-wrap
msgid "shared cache"
msgstr ""

#. type: cindex
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43349
#, no-wrap
msgid "cache, sharing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43358
msgid ""
"Running @command{guix pull}, @command{guix time-machine}, @command{guix "
"system reconfigure}, and @command{guix home reconfigure} pulls the complete "
"Git version control history of your channels in "
"@file{$HOME/.cache/guix/checkouts}.  If you have multiple user accounts "
"(typically @code{root} and a main user account for your personal computer), "
"or if multiple users are using the system (typically on a shared server), "
"then this can quickly waste a lot of space."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43361
msgid ""
"The @code{shared-cache} service lets you prevent this waste by either "
"sharing or exposing a specific user's cache to the other users."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43367
msgid ""
"In the context of this service, @emph{sharing} and @emph{exposing} have the "
"same meaning as with @command{guix shell}: making the shared cache directory"
" read-only if you use mode @option{'expose} (the default), and writable if "
"you use mode @option{'share}, (@pxref{Invoking guix shell, @option{--expose}"
" and @option{--share}})."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43373
msgid ""
"Whatever mode you choose, from the point of view of the user, the cache "
"appears writable.  With @option{'expose}, any write will be stored in a "
"user-owned overlay directory next to mountpoint, whereas with "
"@option{'share}, writes will be propagated back to the sharing user's cache."
msgstr ""

#. type: quotation
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43379
msgid ""
"Use the @option{'share} option @emph{if and only if} users on the machine "
"trust each other.  This is a hard requirement since, with this option, any "
"user could ``poison'' the shared cache to indirectly gain access to other "
"user's data and privileges."
msgstr ""

#. type: quotation
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43386
msgid ""
"Using @option{'share} is meant for a single-seat computer where the single "
"user has unprivileged user accounts---e.g. one for work and one for gaming."
"  Even then, channels from one will leak into the other's cache.  Use with "
"caution."
msgstr ""

#. type: quotation
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43392
msgid ""
"@option{'share} will not work for multiple concurrent invocation of "
"@command{guix}, e.g. if two user accounts run @command{guix time machine} at"
" the same time, the results will be fun but not useful."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43396
msgid ""
"Here is an example configuration that exposes @code{root}'s guix checkout "
"cache to @code{alice} and @code{bob}:"
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43407
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(operating-system\n"
"  ;; @dots{}\n"
"     (services\n"
"      (cons*\n"
"       (service shared-cache-service-type\n"
"             (shared-cache-configuration\n"
"               (users (list (user-cache (user \"alice\"))\n"
"                            (user-cache (user \"bob\"))))))\n"
"                    %desktop-services)))\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43411
msgid ""
"The service can also be extended by providing a list of @code{user-cache}, "
"allowing for easier splitting of configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43420
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(operating-system\n"
"  ;; @dots{}\n"
"  (services\n"
"   (cons*\n"
"    (simple-service 'bob-shared-guix-cache shared-cache-service-type\n"
"                    (list (user-cache (user \"bob\"))))\n"
"    %desktop-services)))\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: defvar
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43422
#, no-wrap
msgid "shared-cache-service-type"
msgstr ""

#. type: defvar
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43425
msgid ""
"Service type for sharing a subdirectory of @file{~/.cache/} between multiple"
" users."
msgstr ""

#. type: defvar
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43432
msgid ""
"This service allows different system users to share the contents of the user"
" cache, avoiding duplication and saving disk space.  It can be configured in"
" either ``share'' mode, where all users write to the same cache, or "
"``expose'' mode, where users get a read-only view with a writable overlay.  "
"Its value must be a @code{shared-cache-configuration} object."
msgstr ""

#. type: deftp
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43434
#, no-wrap
msgid "{Data Type} shared-cache-configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: deftp
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43436
msgid "Data type representing the configuration of the shared cache."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43438
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{mode} (default: @code{'expose})"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43443
msgid ""
"Either @code{'share} (read-write, dangerous) or @code{'expose} (read-only "
"with per-user overlay, the default).  In share mode, all writes go to the "
"shared directory.  In expose mode, only reads use the shared directory; "
"writes go to a user-owned overlay."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43444
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{shared-directory} (default: @code{\"/root/.cache\"})"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43448
msgid ""
"The source cache directory that is shared between users.  Each user will see"
" some or all of its subdirectories mounted into their own @file{~/.cache}."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43449
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{users} (default: @code{'()})"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43452
msgid ""
"The list of users that will benefit from the shared directory.  This must be"
" a list of @code{user-info} records."
msgstr ""

#. type: deftp
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43456
#, no-wrap
msgid "{Data Type} user-info"
msgstr ""

#. type: deftp
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43459
msgid ""
"Data type representing the configuration for a single user benefitting from "
"a shared cache."
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43463
msgid "The username of the user."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43464
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{location} (default: @code{\"/home/@var{user}/.cache\"})"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43466
msgid "The cache directory of the user."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43467 guix-git/doc/guix.texi:44122
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{group} (default: @code{\"users\"})"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43469
msgid "The primary group of the user."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:43470
#, no-wrap
msgid "@code{directories} (default: @code{'(\"guix/checkouts\")})"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
